                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-294-off1497 t18300916-294-crimeloc1500"></join>. The prisoner had worked for me at different times about two months previous to the 26th of August; when he was gone, I missed a great many tools - he had been a labourer; I found him at work for a neighbour, where he had to find his own tools - I found him going from one garden to another, with a pair of barrow straps of mine; he turned round, and tried to escape - I followed him, and took the straps from him; he was locked up - I went to where he had been at work, and found this fork and dibber.</p>
